         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers1316">
               <p>Lowes, who married <persName><ref target="/persons/pers1315.xml"/>Grace
                     Robson</persName> in <date when="1745">1745</date>, served as an exhorter for
                  several years, before becoming a <seg ana="itinerancy">traveling preacher</seg> in
                     <date when="1755">1755</date>. He was obliged to leave the <seg
                     ana="itinerancy">itinerancy</seg> in <date when="1771">1771</date> due to poor
                  health and his refusal to stop selling a medicinal balm he had developed. See
                  Atmore, <hi rend="italic">Memorial</hi>, 244–46; Frank Baker, &apos;Lowes
                  Balsam&apos;, <hi rend="italic">Minutes</hi> (post-Wesley, <date when="1795"
                     >1795</date>), 1:318; <hi rend="italic">MM</hi> 160 (<date when="1947"
                     >1947</date>): 123–25; and <hi rend="italic">Works</hi>, 10:381.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
      </body>
   </text>
